Comment: Hello, With state budget reductions being planned for 2009-2010, my husband and I wanted to take some time to speak to you on behalf of a much needed program that supports children in our local community. The Family, Infant and Preschool Program (FIPP) serves over 1500 children and families in our community annually, not only through home visitations, but also through center-based group programs in Alexander, Burke, and Caldwell counties. FIPP provides support for children who are diagnosed or at-risk for a disability or developmental delay and offers services for families as early as pregnancy and through age 8. In 2008 alone, FIPP served children with autism, attention deficit hyperactivity disorder, cerebral palsy, genetic disorders, hearing impairment, mental retardation, multiple disabilities, developmental delays, communication impairments, orthopedic impairments, pervasive developmental disorder, and traumatic brain injury. FIPP also provides support for children who are considered "typically" developing and/or gifted. Without FIPP, countless families would have no where to turn! FIPP is also a training site for over 75 university students annually from the fields of early education, special education, nursing, physical therapy, occupational therapy, speech-language pathology, psychology, and social work. As a parent of a child who attends FIPP, my heart is breaking knowing this service may no longer be available to my child due to budget cuts. As a Board Certified Music Therapist, I know that early intervention is KEY for children with disabilities - without programs such as FIPP, these children will be lost in the system. My child benefits from the support/teaching provided from the staff at FIPP. My child is exposed to many different children, cultures, disabilities - something that he would not be exposed to any where else and something that has helped to mold him into the person he is today! FIPP is an amazing program that is NEEDED in our community and for our children - please continue to support the Family, Infant and Preschool Program and please continue to support the children in our great state! Thank you for your time and support, Christi, Gary, and Daniel Kreahling

